      "id": 347617,
      "is_answer_order_important": false,
      "stimulus_html": "",
      "stem_html": "One problem with reductive amination as a method of amine synthesis is that by-products are sometimes obtained. For example, reductive amination of benzaldehyde with methylamine leads to a mixture of <i>N</i>-methylbenzylamine and <i>N</i>-methyldibenzylamine. How do you suppose the tertiary amine by-product is formed? Propose a mechanism.",
